<img class="size-full wp-image-1548399 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/WOMAN.jpg?resize=600%2C800&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="600" height="800" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/WOMAN.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/WOMAN.jpg?resize=225%2C300&amp;ssl=1 225w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/WOMAN.jpg?resize=44%2C58&amp;ssl=1 44w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/WOMAN.jpg?resize=146%2C194&amp;ssl=1 146w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/WOMAN.jpg?resize=98%2C130&amp;ssl=1 98w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" />A 56-year-old woman, Alayande Oluwafunmilola Oluwakemi, down with advanced rectal cancer, has pleaded with well-meaning Nigerians for financial assistance to complete her chemotherapy and radiotherapy at the Lagos University Teaching Hospital, Idi-Araba. Oluwakemi needs two million, six thousand naira only to complete chemotherapy. According to her daughter, she stated that her mom’s illness started in 2019 after she lost her dad. “It started like a mild stroke, after few medical attention she was revived back, and she was okay but it was noticed that there was always blood in her stoll. So LASUTH admitted her to surgical emergency, after series of test, she was diagnosed of colorectal cancer. “She did operation in January. She started chemotherapy in September 2020, she is supposed to take 12 sessions but so far, she has taken nine. It was when she wanted to go for the 10th one that it was discovered that her platelet count was low, so presently we are down financial.” A medical report signed by consultant radiation oncologist at LASUTH, Dr Fatiregun B.C. and dated January 15, 2021, confirmed Oluwakemi’s ailment.<img class="size-full wp-image-1548400 aligncenter" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/SAVE-LIFE.jpg?resize=640%2C952&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="952" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/SAVE-LIFE.jpg?w=726&amp;ssl=1 726w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/SAVE-LIFE.jpg?resize=202%2C300&amp;ssl=1 202w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/SAVE-LIFE.jpg?resize=688%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 688w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/SAVE-LIFE.jpg?resize=39%2C58&amp;ssl=1 39w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/SAVE-LIFE.jpg?resize=130%2C194&amp;ssl=1 130w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/SAVE-LIFE.jpg?resize=87%2C130&amp;ssl=1 87w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Donations can be made to Bank Name: FCMB; Account Name: Alayande Oluwafunmilola Oluwakemi; Account Number: 7553604018. Her daughter can be reached via 08168970963 Vanguard News Nigeria Unless there is urgent intervention, 25 years old Serah Osabuohien may not live to fulfill her laudable dreams of becoming one of the best teachers Nigeria has ever produced. This is because Serah needs assistance to continue with her colon cancer (colorectal cancer) treatment at the Lagos University Teaching Hospital,… July 1, 2017 In "Health" We have sold everything we have to treat our daughter and now we have nothing to sell anymore June 23, 2018 In "Health" FOUR-YEAR-OLD Aaishat Dikko is going blind. Retinoblastoma - a devastating eye disorder that is threatening to take her eyesight, has already claimed her left eye. When she was born into the Shamsudin Dikko family, Aaishat weighed a healthy 3.2 kilogrammes. May 10, 2010 In "Health"